<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY WILLIAM DICKEY</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 6 to 8 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons butter </p><p class="no-indent">1 (8-ounce) package sliced baby portobello mushrooms </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup finely minced onion </p><p class="no-indent">1 (16-ounce) package frozen peas </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup water </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon salt </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon ground black pepper </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add mushrooms and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 minutes. Stir in peas and ½ cup water. Cook, stirring frequently, for 8 to 10 minutes or until peas are tender. Stir in salt and pepper.</p></div>
